article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 62, Tulsa 51
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) -- Derrick Bails had 13 points and seven rebounds to lead Arkansas-Little Rock to a 62-51 win over Tulsa on Saturday. Bails was the top scorer for the Trojans (6-1), though he played just 17 minutes in the game. Ben Uzoh had a double-double for Tulsa (2-3), scoring 21 points and adding 10 rebounds -- seven of them on offense. Calvin Walls added 10 points for the Golden Hurricane. Both teams were off the mark in field goals; Arkansas-Little Rock was 20-of-55 for 36 percent and Tulsa shot 31 percent, or 18-of-57. Terrance Akins added 11 points for the Trojans, and De'Andre Eggins had 10 points and eight rebounds.
